						               													<description>The object of the game is to grow the plant with the most leaves. Players each start with an empty flowerpot, then take turns rolling the die to see which color of card they may take. Each face of the die has a colored dot which corresponds to a color of face-down card. The cards will either be a stem (with 0-3 leaves) or a flower, which ends the plant. Once a player's plant is finished, he continues to roll, putting stems he draws in the compost pile (discard pile) and if he draws a flower, he may pick another player's flower to finish. When all flowers are finished, the player with the most leaves on his plant is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
